{"title_page": "A-834,735", "text_new": "{{Drugbox\n| Verifiedfields = changed\n| Watchedfields = changed\n| verifiedrevid = 456505675\n| IUPAC_name = {1-[(Tetrahydro-2''H''-pyran-4-yl)methyl]-1''H''-indol-3-yl}-(2,2,3,3-tetramethylcyclopropyl)methanone\n| image = A-834735_structure.png\n| CAS_number_Ref = {{cascite|changed|??}}\n| CAS_number= 895155-57-4\n| UNII_Ref = {{fdacite|correct|FDA}}\n| UNII = XE27L67C93\n| ATC_prefix=\n| ATC_suffix=\n| ChEMBL_Ref = {{ebicite|correct|EBI}}\n| ChEMBL = 271158\n| PubChem= 11544639\n| DrugBank_Ref = {{drugbankcite|correct|drugbank}}\n| DrugBank=\n| C=22 | H=29 | N=1 | O=2 \n| smiles = C4COCCC4Cn(c3)c2ccccc2c3C(=O)C1C(C)(C)C1(C)C\n| ChemSpiderID_Ref = {{chemspidercite|correct|chemspider}}\n| ChemSpiderID = 9719418\n| StdInChI_Ref = {{stdinchicite|correct|chemspider}}\n| StdInChI=1S/C22H29NO2/c1-21(2)20(22(21,3)4)19(24)17-14-23(13-15-9-11-25-12-10-15)18-8-6-5-7-16(17)18/h5-8,14-15,20H,9-13H2,1-4H3\n| StdInChIKey_Ref = {{stdinchicite|correct|chemspider}}\n| StdInChIKey = NQTMRZNYLIGQCF-UHFFFAOYSA-N\n| bioavailability=\n| metabolism = \n| elimination_half-life= \n| excretion = \n| pregnancy_category =\n| legal_status = \n| routes_of_administration= \n}}\n\n'''A-834,735''' is a drug developed by [[Abbott Laboratories]] that acts as a potent [[cannabinoid]] [[Receptor (biochemistry)|receptor]] [[full agonist]] at both the [[Cannabinoid receptor 1|CB<sub>1</sub>]] and [[Cannabinoid receptor 2|CB<sub>2</sub>]] receptors, with a [[Dissociation constant|''K''<sub>i</sub>]] of 12&nbsp;nM at CB<sub>1</sub> and 0.21&nbsp;nM at CB<sub>2</sub>. Replacing the aromatic 3-benzoyl or 3-naphthoyl group found in most [[indole]] derived cannabinoids, with the 3-tetramethylcyclopropylmethanone group of A-834,735 and related compounds, imparts significant selectivity for CB<sub>2</sub>, with most compounds from this group found to be highly selective CB<sub>2</sub> agonists with little affinity for CB<sub>1</sub>. However low nanomolar CB<sub>1</sub> [[Dissociation constant#Protein-ligand binding|binding affinity]] is retained with certain heterocyclic 1-position substituents such as (''N''-methylpiperidin-2-yl)methyl (cf. [[AM-1220]], [[AM-1248]]), or the (tetrahydropyran-4-yl)methyl substituent of A-834,735, resulting in compounds that still show significant affinity and efficacy at both receptors despite being CB<sub>2</sub> selective overall.<ref>{{cite journal | vauthors = Dart M, Frost J, Tietje K, Daza A, Grayson G, Fan Y, Mukherjee S, Garrison TR, Yao B, Meyer M | display-authors = 6 | date = 2006 | title = 1-Alkyl-3-keto-indoles: identification and in vitro characterization of a series of potent cannabinoid ligands. | journal = 2006 Symposium on the Cannabinoids | publisher = International Cannabinoid Research Society | location = Burlington, VT }}</ref><ref>{{cite journal | vauthors = Poso A, Huffman JW | title = Targeting the cannabinoid CB2 receptor: modelling and structural determinants of CB2 selective ligands | journal = British Journal of Pharmacology | volume = 153 | issue = 2 | pages = 335\u201346 | date = January 2008 | pmid = 17982473 | pmc = 2219524 | doi = 10.1038/sj.bjp.0707567 }}</ref><ref name=\"pmid17965748\">{{cite journal | vauthors = Chin CL, Tovcimak AE, Hradil VP, Seifert TR, Hollingsworth PR, Chandran P, Zhu CZ, Gauvin D, Pai M, Wetter J, Hsieh GC, Honore P, Frost JM, Dart MJ, Meyer MD, Yao BB, Cox BF, Fox GB | display-authors = 6 | title = Differential effects of cannabinoid receptor agonists on regional brain activity using pharmacological MRI | journal = British Journal of Pharmacology | volume = 153 | issue = 2 | pages = 367\u201379 | date = January 2008 | pmid = 17965748 | pmc = 2219521 | doi = 10.1038/sj.bjp.0707506 }}</ref><ref>{{cite journal | vauthors = Frost JM, Dart MJ, Tietje KR, Garrison TR, Grayson GK, Daza AV, El-Kouhen OF, Miller LN, Li L, Yao BB, Hsieh GC, Pai M, Zhu CZ, Chandran P, Meyer MD | display-authors = 6 | title = Indol-3-yl-tetramethylcyclopropyl ketones: effects of indole ring substitution on CB2 cannabinoid receptor activity | journal = Journal of Medicinal Chemistry | volume = 51 | issue = 6 | pages = 1904\u201312 | date = March 2008 | pmid = 18311894 | doi = 10.1021/jm7011613 }}\n</ref><ref>{{cite journal | vauthors = Frost JM, Dart MJ, Tietje KR, Garrison TR, Grayson GK, Daza AV, El-Kouhen OF, Yao BB, Hsieh GC, Pai M, Zhu CZ, Chandran P, Meyer MD | display-authors = 6 | title = Indol-3-ylcycloalkyl ketones: effects of N1 substituted indole side chain variations on CB(2) cannabinoid receptor activity | journal = Journal of Medicinal Chemistry | volume = 53 | issue = 1 | pages = 295\u2013315 | date = January 2010 | pmid = 19921781 | doi = 10.1021/jm901214q }}\n</ref>\n\n==Legal status==\n\nAs of October 2015 A-834,735 is a controlled substance in China.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.sfda.gov.cn/WS01/CL0056/130753.html | title=\u5173\u4e8e\u5370\u53d1\u300a\u975e\u836f\u7528\u7c7b\u9ebb\u9189\u836f\u54c1\u548c\u7cbe\u795e\u836f\u54c1\u5217\u7ba1\u529e\u6cd5\u300b\u7684\u901a\u77e5 | publisher=China Food and Drug Administration | date=27 September 2015 | language=Chinese | access-date=1 October 2015}}</ref>\n\n== See also ==\n* [[A-796,260]]\n* [[AB-001]]\n* [[AB-005]]\n* [[FUB-144]]\n* [[JTE 7-31]]\n* [[UR-144]]\n* [[XLR-11 (drug)|XLR-11]]\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Cannabinoids}}\n\n[[Category:Cannabinoids]]\n[[Category:Tetrahydropyrans]]\n[[Category:Cyclopropanes]]\n[[Category:Tetramethylcyclopropanoylindoles]]\n", "text_old": "{{Drugbox\n| Verifiedfields = changed\n| Watchedfields = changed\n| verifiedrevid = 456505675\n| IUPAC_name = {1-[(Tetrahydro-2''H''-pyran-4-yl)methyl]-1''H''-indol-3-yl}-(2,2,3,3-tetramethylcyclopropyl)methanone\n| image = A-834735_structure.png\n| CAS_number_Ref = {{cascite|changed|??}}\n| CAS_number= 895155-57-4\n| ATC_prefix=\n| ATC_suffix=\n| ChEMBL_Ref = {{ebicite|correct|EBI}}\n| ChEMBL = 271158\n| PubChem= 11544639\n| DrugBank_Ref = {{drugbankcite|correct|drugbank}}\n| DrugBank=\n| C=22 | H=29 | N=1 | O=2 \n| smiles = C4COCCC4Cn(c3)c2ccccc2c3C(=O)C1C(C)(C)C1(C)C\n| ChemSpiderID_Ref = {{chemspidercite|correct|chemspider}}\n| ChemSpiderID = 9719418\n| StdInChI_Ref = {{stdinchicite|correct|chemspider}}\n| StdInChI=1S/C22H29NO2/c1-21(2)20(22(21,3)4)19(24)17-14-23(13-15-9-11-25-12-10-15)18-8-6-5-7-16(17)18/h5-8,14-15,20H,9-13H2,1-4H3\n| StdInChIKey_Ref = {{stdinchicite|correct|chemspider}}\n| StdInChIKey = NQTMRZNYLIGQCF-UHFFFAOYSA-N\n| bioavailability=\n| metabolism = \n| elimination_half-life= \n| excretion = \n| pregnancy_category =\n| legal_status = \n| routes_of_administration= \n}}\n\n'''A-834,735''' is a drug developed by [[Abbott Laboratories]] that acts as a potent [[cannabinoid]] [[Receptor (biochemistry)|receptor]] [[full agonist]] at both the [[Cannabinoid receptor 1|CB<sub>1</sub>]] and [[Cannabinoid receptor 2|CB<sub>2</sub>]] receptors, with a [[Dissociation constant|''K''<sub>i</sub>]] of 12&nbsp;nM at CB<sub>1</sub> and 0.21&nbsp;nM at CB<sub>2</sub>. Replacing the aromatic 3-benzoyl or 3-naphthoyl group found in most [[indole]] derived cannabinoids, with the 3-tetramethylcyclopropylmethanone group of A-834,735 and related compounds, imparts significant selectivity for CB<sub>2</sub>, with most compounds from this group found to be highly selective CB<sub>2</sub> agonists with little affinity for CB<sub>1</sub>. However low nanomolar CB<sub>1</sub> [[Dissociation constant#Protein-ligand binding|binding affinity]] is retained with certain heterocyclic 1-position substituents such as (''N''-methylpiperidin-2-yl)methyl (cf. [[AM-1220]], [[AM-1248]]), or the (tetrahydropyran-4-yl)methyl substituent of A-834,735, resulting in compounds that still show significant affinity and efficacy at both receptors despite being CB<sub>2</sub> selective overall.<ref>{{cite journal | vauthors = Dart M, Frost J, Tietje K, Daza A, Grayson G, Fan Y, Mukherjee S, Garrison TR, Yao B, Meyer M | display-authors = 6 | date = 2006 | title = 1-Alkyl-3-keto-indoles: identification and in vitro characterization of a series of potent cannabinoid ligands. | journal = 2006 Symposium on the Cannabinoids | publisher = International Cannabinoid Research Society | location = Burlington, VT }}</ref><ref>{{cite journal | vauthors = Poso A, Huffman JW | title = Targeting the cannabinoid CB2 receptor: modelling and structural determinants of CB2 selective ligands | journal = British Journal of Pharmacology | volume = 153 | issue = 2 | pages = 335\u201346 | date = January 2008 | pmid = 17982473 | pmc = 2219524 | doi = 10.1038/sj.bjp.0707567 }}</ref><ref name=\"pmid17965748\">{{cite journal | vauthors = Chin CL, Tovcimak AE, Hradil VP, Seifert TR, Hollingsworth PR, Chandran P, Zhu CZ, Gauvin D, Pai M, Wetter J, Hsieh GC, Honore P, Frost JM, Dart MJ, Meyer MD, Yao BB, Cox BF, Fox GB | display-authors = 6 | title = Differential effects of cannabinoid receptor agonists on regional brain activity using pharmacological MRI | journal = British Journal of Pharmacology | volume = 153 | issue = 2 | pages = 367\u201379 | date = January 2008 | pmid = 17965748 | pmc = 2219521 | doi = 10.1038/sj.bjp.0707506 }}</ref><ref>{{cite journal | vauthors = Frost JM, Dart MJ, Tietje KR, Garrison TR, Grayson GK, Daza AV, El-Kouhen OF, Miller LN, Li L, Yao BB, Hsieh GC, Pai M, Zhu CZ, Chandran P, Meyer MD | display-authors = 6 | title = Indol-3-yl-tetramethylcyclopropyl ketones: effects of indole ring substitution on CB2 cannabinoid receptor activity | journal = Journal of Medicinal Chemistry | volume = 51 | issue = 6 | pages = 1904\u201312 | date = March 2008 | pmid = 18311894 | doi = 10.1021/jm7011613 }}\n</ref><ref>{{cite journal | vauthors = Frost JM, Dart MJ, Tietje KR, Garrison TR, Grayson GK, Daza AV, El-Kouhen OF, Yao BB, Hsieh GC, Pai M, Zhu CZ, Chandran P, Meyer MD | display-authors = 6 | title = Indol-3-ylcycloalkyl ketones: effects of N1 substituted indole side chain variations on CB(2) cannabinoid receptor activity | journal = Journal of Medicinal Chemistry | volume = 53 | issue = 1 | pages = 295\u2013315 | date = January 2010 | pmid = 19921781 | doi = 10.1021/jm901214q }}\n</ref>\n\n==Legal status==\n\nAs of October 2015 A-834,735 is a controlled substance in China.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.sfda.gov.cn/WS01/CL0056/130753.html | title=\u5173\u4e8e\u5370\u53d1\u300a\u975e\u836f\u7528\u7c7b\u9ebb\u9189\u836f\u54c1\u548c\u7cbe\u795e\u836f\u54c1\u5217\u7ba1\u529e\u6cd5\u300b\u7684\u901a\u77e5 | publisher=China Food and Drug Administration | date=27 September 2015 | language=Chinese | access-date=1 October 2015}}</ref>\n\n== See also ==\n* [[A-796,260]]\n* [[AB-001]]\n* [[AB-005]]\n* [[FUB-144]]\n* [[JTE 7-31]]\n* [[UR-144]]\n* [[XLR-11 (drug)|XLR-11]]\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Cannabinoids}}\n\n[[Category:Cannabinoids]]\n[[Category:Tetrahydropyrans]]\n[[Category:Cyclopropanes]]\n[[Category:Tetramethylcyclopropanoylindoles]]\n", "name_user": "Fswitzer4", "label": "safe", "comment": "added FDA UNII to drug box", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/A-834,735"}
{"title_page": "Qasem-e Anvar", "text_new": "'''Q\u0101sem-e Anv\u0101r''' (Q\u0101sim-i Anw\u0101r) ({{lang-fa|\u0642\u0627\u0633\u0645 \u0627\u0646\u0648\u0627\u0631}}; 1356 \u2013 1433) was an [[Iran|Iranian]] poet and [[Sufi]]. Q\u0101sem-e Anw\u0101r wrote \u1e21azals, molamma\u02bfs, and tuyu\u1e21s in a simple [[Azerbaijani language|Azeri Turkish]].<ref name=\"iranica\">''H. Javadi and K. Burrill''. [http://www.iranicaonline.org/articles/azerbaijan-x Azeri Turkish Literature]</ref> He was a Timurid propagandist and was born in [[Sarab, East Azerbaijan|Sarab]], [[Tabriz]].<ref>[http://www.noormags.com/view/Magazine/ViewPages.aspx?ArticleId=160827 \u0642\u0627\u0633\u0645 \u0627\u0646\u0648\u0627\u0631 \u0648 \u063a\u0632\u0644\u06cc \u06a9\u0647 \u0628\u0632\u0628\u0627\u0646 \u06af\u06cc\u0644\u06a9\u06cc \u0633\u0631\u0648\u062f\u0647 ,\u0645\u062c\u0644\u0647 \u0627\u0631\u0645\u063a\u0627\u0646 , \u062f\u0648\u0631\u0647 \u0628\u06cc\u0633\u062a \u0648 \u0634\u0634\u0645\u060c \u062a\u06cc\u0631 1336 - \u0634\u0645\u0627\u0631\u0647 4 , \u0635\u0641\u062d\u0647 179 , \u062a\u0635\u0648\u06cc\u0631 | \u067e\u0627\u06cc\u06af\u0627\u0647 \u0645\u062c\u0644\u0627\u062a \u062a\u062e\u0635\u0635\u06cc \u0646\u0648\u0631]</ref>\n\nQasem-e Anar is the author of a popular [[Masnavi]] entitled [[Anis al-arifin]] (Mystics' Companion), an explanation of Sufi terminology, and also a [[Diwan (poetry)|divan]] of Sufi poetry.<ref>Thackston, Wheeler McIntosh. 1994. A millennium of classical Persian poetry a guide to the reading & understanding of Persian poetry from the tenth to the twentieth century. Bethesda, Md: Ibex publishers. p. 69.</ref>\n\nA well-known Sufi sheikh who had a large following in [[Herat]], Q\u0101sem-e Anvar was suspected of collaboration with an assailant who stabbed [[Shah Rukh (Timurid dynasty)|Shahrukh]] and was banished from Herat.<ref>Thackston, Wheeler McIntosh. 1994. p.69.</ref>\n\nQasem-e Anvar also spent many years in [[Gilan]] and learnt the vernacular of the region and has even a [[ghazal]] in [[Gilaki language|Gilaki]].\n\n==Poetry==\n{{Verse translation|italicsoff=y|rtl1=y|\n{{lang|fa|rtl=yes|\u0627\u0632 \u0647\u0631 \u0637\u0631\u0641\u06cc \u0686\u0647\u0631\u0647 \u06af\u0634\u0627\u06cc\u06cc \u06a9\u0647 \u0645\u0646\u0645\n\u062f\u0631 \u0647\u0631 \u0635\u0641\u062a\u06cc \u062c\u0644\u0648\u0647\u200c\u06af\u0631 \u0622\u06cc\u06cc \u06a9\u0647 \u0645\u0646\u0645\n\u0628\u0627 \u0627\u06cc\u0646\u0647\u0645\u0647 \u06af\u0647\u06af\u0627\u0647 \u063a\u0644\u0637 \u0645\u06cc\u200c\u0627\u0641\u062a\u0645}}\n<ref>http://www.mibosearch.com/word.aspx?wName=%D9%82%D8%A7%D8%B3%D9%85+%D8%A7%D9%86%D9%88%D8%A7%D8%B1</ref>{{lang|fa|rtl=yes|\u0646\u0627\u062f\u0627\u0646 \u06a9\u0633 \u0648 \u0628\u0644\u0647 \u0631\u0648\u0633\u062a\u0627\u06cc\u06cc \u06a9\u0647 \u0645\u0646\u0645}}\n|\nYou show me your face everywhere I see\nand you try to get any good attribute\nso I sometimes make a mistake that's why\nI am an ignorant person or maybe I'm rural}}\n\n==References==\n<references/>\n{{Azerbaijani Turkic literature}}\n\n{{Wikiquote}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Qasem Anwar}}\n[[Category:Azerbaijani-language poets]]\n[[Category:Persian-language poets]]\n[[Category:People from Torbat-e Jam]]\n[[Category:People from Tabriz]]\n[[Category:1426 deaths]]\n[[Category:1365 births]]\n[[Category:People from Sarab]]\n\n\n{{Azerbaijan-poet-stub}}\n", "text_old": "'''Q\u0101sem-e Anv\u0101r''' (Q\u0101sim-i Anw\u0101r) ({{lang-fa|\u0642\u0627\u0633\u0645 \u0627\u0646\u0648\u0627\u0631}}; 1356 \u2013 1433) was an [[Iran|Iranian]] poet and [[Sufi]]. Q\u0101sem-e Anw\u0101r wrote \u1e21azals, molamma\u02bfs, and tuyu\u1e21s in a simple [[Azerbaijani language|Azeri Turkish]].<ref name=\"iranica\">''H. Javadi and K. Burrill''. [http://www.iranicaonline.org/articles/azerbaijan-x Azeri Turkish Literature]</ref> He was a Timurid propagandist and was born in [[Sarab, East Azerbaijan|Sarab]], [[Tabriz]].<ref>[http://www.noormags.com/view/Magazine/ViewPages.aspx?ArticleId=160827 \u0642\u0627\u0633\u0645 \u0627\u0646\u0648\u0627\u0631 \u0648 \u063a\u0632\u0644\u06cc \u06a9\u0647 \u0628\u0632\u0628\u0627\u0646 \u06af\u06cc\u0644\u06a9\u06cc \u0633\u0631\u0648\u062f\u0647 ,\u0645\u062c\u0644\u0647 \u0627\u0631\u0645\u063a\u0627\u0646 , \u062f\u0648\u0631\u0647 \u0628\u06cc\u0633\u062a \u0648 \u0634\u0634\u0645\u060c \u062a\u06cc\u0631 1336 - \u0634\u0645\u0627\u0631\u0647 4 , \u0635\u0641\u062d\u0647 179 , \u062a\u0635\u0648\u06cc\u0631 | \u067e\u0627\u06cc\u06af\u0627\u0647 \u0645\u062c\u0644\u0627\u062a \u062a\u062e\u0635\u0635\u06cc \u0646\u0648\u0631]</ref>\n\nQasem-e Anar is the author of a popular [[Masnavi]] entitled [[Anis al-arifin]] (Mystics' Companion), an explanation of Sufi terminology, and also a [[Diwan (poetry)|divan]] of Sufi poetry.<ref>Thackston, Wheeler McIntosh. 1994. A millennium of classical Persian poetry a guide to the reading & understanding of Persian poetry from the tenth to the twentieth century. Bethesda, Md: Ibex publishers. p. 69.</ref>\n\nA well-known Sufi sheikh who had a large following in [[Herat]], Q\u0101sem-e Anvar was suspected of collaboration with an assailant who stabbed [[Shah Rukh (Timurid dynasty)|Shahrukh]] and was banished from Herat.<ref>Thackston, Wheeler McIntosh. 1994. p.69.</ref>\n\nQasem-e Anvar also spent many years in [[Gilan]] and learnt the vernacular of the region and has even a [[ghazal]] in [[Gilaki language|Gilaki]].\n\n==Poetry==\n{{Verse translation|italicsoff=y|rtl1=y|\n{{lang|fa|rtl=yes|\u0627\u0632 \u0647\u0631 \u0637\u0631\u0641\u06cc \u0686\u0647\u0631\u0647 \u06af\u0634\u0627\u06cc\u06cc \u06a9\u0647 \u0645\u0646\u0645\n\u062f\u0631 \u0647\u0631 \u0635\u0641\u062a\u06cc \u062c\u0644\u0648\u0647\u200c\u06af\u0631 \u0622\u06cc\u06cc \u06a9\u0647 \u0645\u0646\u0645\n\u0628\u0627 \u0627\u06cc\u0646\u0647\u0645\u0647 \u06af\u0647\u06af\u0627\u0647 \u063a\u0644\u0637 \u0645\u06cc\u200c\u0627\u0641\u062a\u0645}}\n<ref>http://www.mibosearch.com/word.aspx?wName=%D9%82%D8%A7%D8%B3%D9%85+%D8%A7%D9%86%D9%88%D8%A7%D8%B1</ref>{{lang|fa|rtl=yes|\u0646\u0627\u062f\u0627\u0646 \u06a9\u0633 \u0648 \u0628\u0644\u0647 \u0631\u0648\u0633\u062a\u0627\u06cc\u06cc \u06a9\u0647 \u0645\u0646\u0645}}\n|\nYou show me your face everywhere I see\nand you try to get any good attribute\nso I sometimes make a mistake that's why\nI am an ignorant person or maybe I'm rural}}\n\n==References==\n<references/>\n{{Azerbaijani Turkic literature}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Qasem Anwar}}\n[[Category:Azerbaijani-language poets]]\n[[Category:Persian-language poets]]\n[[Category:People from Torbat-e Jam]]\n[[Category:People from Tabriz]]\n[[Category:1426 deaths]]\n[[Category:1365 births]]\n[[Category:People from Sarab]]\n\n\n{{Azerbaijan-poet-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Vilho-Veli", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(Link)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Qasem-e_Anvar"}
{"title_page": "1934\u201335 F.B.C. Juventus season", "text_new": "{{Infobox football club season\n|club = [[Juventus|Foot-Ball Club Juventus]]\n|season = 1934-35\n|manager = [[Carlo Carcano]]<br> (until 16 December 1934)<br />[[Carlo Bigatto]]\n|chairman = [[Edoardo Agnelli]]\n|chrtitle=President\n|stadium= [[Stadio Olimpico Grande Torino|Stadio Benito Mussolini]]\n|league = [[Serie A]]\n|league result = [[1934-35 Serie A|1\u00ba]] (in [[1935 Mitropa Cup]])\n|cup2 = [[Mitropa Cup]]\n|cup2 result = [[1935 Mitropa Cup|Semifinals]]\n|league topscorer = [[Felice Borel|Borel II]] (14)\n|season topscorer = Borel II (20)\n\n|pattern_la1 = _juve2\n|leftarm1 = ffffff\n|pattern_b1 =_juve193236h\n|body1 = ffffff\n|pattern_ra1 = _juve2\n|rightarm1 = ffffff\n|shorts1 = ffffff\n|pattern_so1 = _juve\n|socks1 = 000000\n\n|prevseason = [[1933-34 Juventus F.C. season|1933-34]]\n|nextseason = [[1935-36 Juventus F.C. season|1935-36]]\n}}\nDuring the 1934\u201335 season '''Foot-Ball Club Juventus''' competed in [[Serie A]] and [[Mitropa Cup]].\n\n== Summary ==\nThe club won the fifth title in a row.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.archiviolastampa.it/component/option,com_lastampa/task,search/mod,libera/action,viewer/Itemid,3/page,3/articleid,1138_01_1935_0132A_0003_24911531/|title=La Juventus si riconferma campione d'Italia|publisher=La Stampa|date=3 June 1935|p=3}}</ref>\nA unique achievement only surpassed until 2017 by the same club <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.juventus.com/es/news/jspeciali/scudetto20152016/i-due-quinquenni-juventus-1935-2016-scudetto.php|title=quinquenni|publisher=myjuve.it}}</ref>\nIn December 1934 coach Carcano was suddenly removed from the Juventus club in order to stifle a homosexual scandal<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.laspecula.com/oldwebsite/sport_publ/omosessualit%E0_nello_sport_un_tab%F9_da_sfatare.htm|title=Carcano Out of Juventus|publisher=laspecula.com}}</ref> in which he was involved by elements of society hostile to him.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.carlinsboys.com/storia.html |title=Archived copy |accessdate=21 February 2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150923200520/http://www.carlinsboys.com/storia.html |archivedate=23 September 2015 }}</ref>\nBigatto returned to Juventus in a managerial role during the latter part of the season in which Juventus won the league over Inter by two points; before Virginio Rosetta took over the team in June.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.forza-juventus.com/biographies/bigatto.htm|publisher= Forza-Juventus.com|date=September 28, 2007|title=Season 34-35 }}</ref>\n\n== Squad ==\n{{fs start}}\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ITA|name=[[Attilio Bulgheri]]|pos=GK}}\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ITA|name=[[Eugenio Staccione]]|pos=GK}}\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ITA|name=[[Cesare Valinasso]]|pos=GK}}\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ITA|name=[[Umberto Caligaris]]|pos=DF}}\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ITA|name=[[Alfredo Foni]]|pos=DF}}\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ITA|name=[[Virginio Rosetta]]|pos=DF}}\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ITA|name=[[Giovanni Varglien|Varglien II]]|pos=DF}}\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ITA|name=[[Luigi Bertolini]]|pos=MF}}\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ITA|name=[[Teobaldo Depetrini]]|pos=MF}}\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ARG|name=[[Luis Monti]]|pos=MF}}\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ITA|name=[[Gastone Prendato]]|pos=MF}}<ref>Transfered In for [[1935 Mitropa Cup]].</ref>\n{{fs mid}}\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ITA|name=[[Luciano Ramella]]|pos=MF}}\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ITA|name=[[Pietro Serantoni]]|pos=MF}}\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ITA|name=[[Mario Varglien|Varglien I]]|pos=MF}}\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ITA|name=[[Felice Borel|Borel II]]|pos=FW}}\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ITA|name=[[Lino Cason]]|pos=FW}}\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ARG|name=[[Renato Cesarini]]|pos=FW}}\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ITA|name=[[Armando Diena|Diena II]]|pos=FW}}\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ITA|name=[[Giovanni Ferrari]]|pos=FW}}\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ITA|name=[[Guglielmo Gabetto]]|pos=FW}}\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ARG|name=''[[Raimundo Orsi]]''|pos=FW}}<ref>Released on April 1935,</ref><ref>{{ci