all Club Juventus]]\n|season = 1934-35\n|manager = [[Carlo Carcano]] (until December 1934)<br />[[Carlo Bigatto]]\n|chairman = [[Edoardo Agnelli]]\n|chrtitle=President\n|stadium= [[Stadio Olimpico Grande Torino|Stadio Benito Mussolini]]\n|league = [[Serie A]]\n|league result = [[1934-35 Serie A|1\u00ba]] (in [[1935 Mitropa Cup]])\n|cup2 = [[Mitropa Cup]]\n|cup2 result = [[1935 Mitropa Cup|Semifinals]]\n|league topscorer = [[Felice Borel|Borel II]] (14)\n|season topscorer = Borel II (20)\n\n|pattern_la1 = _juve2\n|leftarm1 = ffffff\n|pattern_b1 =_juve193236h\n|body1 = ffffff\n|pattern_ra1 = _juve2\n|rightarm1 = ffffff\n|shorts1 = ffffff\n|pattern_so1 = _juve\n|socks1 = 000000\n\n|prevseason = [[1933-34 Juventus F.C. season|1933-34]]\n|nextseason = [[1935-36 Juventus F.C. season|1935-36]]\n}}\nDuring the 1934\u201335 season '''Foot-Ball Club Juventus''' competed in [[Serie A]] and [[Mitropa Cup]].\n\n== Summary ==\nThe club won the fifth title in a row.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.archiviolastampa.it/component/option,com_lastampa/task,search/mod,libera/action,viewer/Itemid,3/page,3/articleid,1138_01_1935_0132A_0003_24911531/|title=La Juventus si riconferma campione d'Italia|publisher=La Stampa|date=3 June 1935|p=3}}</ref>\nA unique achievement only surpassed until 2017 by the same club <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.juventus.com/es/news/jspeciali/scudetto20152016/i-due-quinquenni-juventus-1935-2016-scudetto.php|title=quinquenni|publisher=myjuve.it}}</ref>\nIn December 1934 coach Carcano was suddenly removed from the Juventus club in order to stifle a homosexual scandal<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.laspecula.com/oldwebsite/sport_publ/omosessualit%E0_nello_sport_un_tab%F9_da_sfatare.htm|title=Carcano Out of Juventus|publisher=laspecula.com}}</ref> in which he was involved by elements of society hostile to him.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.carlinsboys.com/storia.html |title=Archived copy |accessdate=21 February 2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150923200520/http://www.carlinsboys.com/storia.html |archivedate=23 September 2015 }}</ref>\nBigatto returned to Juventus in a managerial role during the latter part of the season in which Juventus won the league over Inter by two points; before Virginio Rosetta took over the team in June.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.forza-juventus.com/biographies/bigatto.htm|publisher= Forza-Juventus.com|date=September 28, 2007|title=Season 34-35 }}</ref>\n\n== Squad ==\n{{fs start}}\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ITA|name=[[Attilio Bulgheri]]|pos=GK}}\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ITA|name=[[Eugenio Staccione]]|pos=GK}}\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ITA|name=[[Cesare Valinasso]]|pos=GK}}\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ITA|name=[[Umberto Caligaris]]|pos=DF}}\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ITA|name=[[Alfredo Foni]]|pos=DF}}\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ITA|name=[[Virginio Rosetta]]|pos=DF}}\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ITA|name=[[Giovanni Varglien|Varglien II]]|pos=DF}}\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ITA|name=[[Luigi Bertolini]]|pos=MF}}\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ITA|name=[[Teobaldo Depetrini]]|pos=MF}}\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ARG|name=[[Luis Monti]]|pos=MF}}\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ITA|name=[[Gastone Prendato]]|pos=MF}}<ref>Transfered In for [[1935 Mitropa Cup]].</ref>\n{{fs mid}}\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ITA|name=[[Luciano Ramella]]|pos=MF}}\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ITA|name=[[Pietro Serantoni]]|pos=MF}}\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ITA|name=[[Mario Varglien|Varglien I]]|pos=MF}}\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ITA|name=[[Felice Borel|Borel II]]|pos=FW}}\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ITA|name=[[Lino Cason]]|pos=FW}}\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ARG|name=[[Renato Cesarini]]|pos=FW}}\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ITA|name=[[Armando Diena|Diena II]]|pos=FW}}\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ITA|name=[[Giovanni Ferrari]]|pos=FW}}\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ITA|name=[[Guglielmo Gabetto]]|pos=FW}}\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ARG|name=''[[Raimundo Orsi]]''|pos=FW}}<ref>Released on April 1935,</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.archiviolastampa.it/component/option,com_lastampa/task,search/mod,libera/action,viewer/Itemid,3/page,7/articleid,1137_01_1935_0081_0007_24910733/|title=Orsi torna in Argentina|publisher=La Stampa|date=4 April 1935|p=7}}</ref>\n{{fs player|no=|nat=ITA|name=[[Alberto Tiberti]]|pos=FW}}\n{{fs end}}\n\n== Competitions ==\n=== Serie A ===\n{{main|1934-35 Serie A}}\n\n====League table====\n{{:1934-35 Serie A|showteam=JUV}}\n\n==== Matches ====\n{{footballbox collapsible\n|date = 30 September 1934\n|round = 1\n|time = \n|team1 = [[Brescia Calcio|Brescia]]\n|team2 = Juventus\n|score = 0-2\n|report=http://calcio-seriea.net/tabellini/1934/1533/\n|location = [[Brescia]]\n|stadium = [[Stadium di Viale Piave]]\n|attendance =\n|referee = Giuseppe Scarpi\n|goals1 = \n|goals2 = {{Goal|66}} [[Felice Borel|Borel II]]<br />{{Goal|74}} [[Pietro Serantoni|Serantoni]]\n|result = W\n}}\n{{footballbox collapsible\n|date = 7 October 1934\n|round = 2\n|time = \n|team1 = Juventus\n|team2 = [[S.S.C. Napoli|Napoli]]\n|score = 2-1\n|report=http://calcio-seriea.net/tabellini/1934/1615/\n|location = [[Torino]]\n|stadium = [[Stadio Olimpico Grande Torino|Stadio Benito Mussolini]]\n|attendance =\n|referee = [[Raffaele Mastellari|Mastellari]]\n|goals1 = [[Felice Borel|Borel II]] {{Goal|60}}<br />[[Giovanni Ferrari|Ferrari]] {{Goal|82}}\n|goals2 = {{Goal|10}} [[Pietro Ferraris|Ferraris II]]\n|result =W\n}}\n{{footballbox collapsible\n|date = 14 October 1934\n|round = 3\n|time = \n|team1 = [[Sampierdarenese]]\n|team2 = Juventus\n|score = 0-1\n|report=http://calcio-seriea.net/tabellini/1934/1703/\n|location = [[Genova]]\n|stadium = [[Stadio del Littorio]]\n|attendance =\n|referee = [[Rinaldo Barlassina|Barlassina]]\n|goals1 = \n|goals2 = {{Goal|50}} [[Giovanni Ferrari|Ferrari]]\n|result =W\n}}\n{{footballbox collapsible\n|date = 21 October 1934\n|round = 4\n|time = \n|team1 = Juventus\n|team2 = [[Torino F.C.|Torino]]\n|score = 1-1\n|report=http://calcio-seriea.net/tabellini/1934/1553/\n|location = [[Torino]]\n|stadium = [[Stadio Olimpico Grande Torino|Stadio Benito Mussolini]]\n|attendance =\n|referee = [[Raffaele Scorzoni|Scorzoni]]\n|goals1 = [[Felice Borel|Borel II]] {{Goal|53}}\n|goals2 = {{Goal|6}} [[Fioravante Baldi|Baldi III]]\n|result =D\n}}\n{{footballbox collapsible\n|date = 4 November 1934\n|round = 5\n|time = \n|team1 = [[S.S. Lazio|Lazio]]\n|team2 = Juventus\n|score = 5-3\n|report=http://calcio-seriea.net/tabellini/1934/1631/\n|location = [[Rome|Roma]]\n|stadium = [[Stadio Nazionale|Stadio Nazionale del PNF]]\n|attendance =\n|referee = Giuseppe Turbiani\n|goals1 = [[Silvio Piola|Piola]] {{Goal|37||78}}<br />[[Jo\u00e3o Fantoni|Fantoni I]] {{Goal|38}}<br />[[Alejandro Demar\u00eda|Demar\u00eda]] {{Goal|50}}<br />[[Virgilio Felice Levratto|Levratto]] {{Goal|74}}\n|goals2 = {{Goal|15}} [[Renato Cesarini|Cesarini]]<br />{{Goal|79||89}} [[Pietro Serantoni|Serantoni]]\n|result =L\n}}\n{{footballbox collapsible\n|date = 18 November 1934\n|round = 6\n|time = \n|team1 = Juventus\n|team2 = [[Inter Milan|Ambrosiana-Inter]]\n|score = 1-0\n|report=http://calcio-seriea.net/tabellini/1934/1713/\n|location = [[Torino]]\n|stadium = [[Stadio Olimpico Grande Torino|Stadio Benito Mussolini]]\n|attendance =\n|referee = Mario Ciamberlini\n|goals1 = [[Giovanni Ferrari|Ferrari]] {{Goal|69}}\n|goals2 = \n|result =W\n}}\n{{footballbox collapsible\n|date = 25 November 1934\n|round = 7\n|time = \n|team1 = Livorno\n|team2 = Juventus\n|score = 1-2\n|report=http://calcio-seriea.net/tabellini/1934/1567/\n|location = [[Livorno]]\n|stadium = [[Stadio Armando Picchi|Stadio Edda Ciano Mussolini]]\n|attendance =\n|referee = Umberto Levrero\n|goals1 = [[Giovanni Busoni|Busoni]] {{Goal|13}}\n|goals2 = {{Goal|68}} [[Pietro Serantoni|Serantoni]]<br />{{Goal|87}} [[Felice Borel|Borel II]]\n|result =W\n}}\n{{footballbox collapsible\n|date = 2 December 1934\n|round = 8\n|time = \n|team1 = Juventus\n|team2 = Triestina\n|score = 0-0\n|report=http://calcio-seriea.net/tabellini/1934/1649/\n|location = [[Torino]]\n|stadium = [[Stadio Olimpico Grande Torino|Stadio Benito Mussolini]]\n|attendance =\n|referee