lagicon|HUN|1918}}Mih\u00e1ly Iv\u00e1ncsics\n|goals1 = [[Vladim\u00edr B\u00edna|B\u00edna]] {{Goal|19}}<br />[[Anton\u00edn Bir\u00f3|Bir\u00f3]] {{Goal|36}}<br />[[Karel Hes|Hes]] {{Goal|61}}\n|goals2 = {{Goal|25||62}} [[Felice Borel|Borel II]]<br />{{Goal|33}} [[Giovanni Ferrari|Ferrari]]\n|result =D\n}}\n\n{{footballbox collapsible\n|date = 23 June 1935\n|round = \n|time = \n|team1 = Juventus\n|team2 = {{flagicon|HUN|1918}}[[Viktoria Plzen]]\n|score = 5-1\n|report=\n|location = [[Torino]]\n|stadium = [[Stadio Olimpico Grande Torino|Stadio Benito Mussolini]]\n|attendance =\n|referee = {{flagicon|AUT}} Alois Beranek\n|goals1 = [[Giovanni Ferrari|Ferrari]] {{Goal|6||87}}<br />[[Felice Borel|Borel II]] {{Goal|25||69}}<br />[[Armando Diena|Diena II]] {{Goal|39}}\n|goals2 = {{Goal|80}} [[V\u00e1clav Hor\u00e1k|Hor\u00e1k]]\n|result =W\n}}\n\n==== Quarterfinals ====\n{{footballbox collapsible\n|date= 30 June 1935\n|round = \n|time = \n|team1 = {{flagicon|HUN}}[[MTK Hungaria]]\n|team2 = Juventus\n|score = 1-3\n|report=\n|location = [[Budapest]]\n|stadium = [[N\u00e1ndor Hidegkuti Stadion|Hung\u00e1ria k\u00f6r\u00fat]]\n|attendance =\n|referee = {{flagicon|AUT}} Alois Beranek\n|goals1 = [[Heinrich M\u00fcller (calciatore 1909)|M\u00fcller]] {{Goal|75|rig.}}\n|goals2 = {{Goal|51}} [[Giovanni Ferrari|Ferrari]]<br />{{Goal|65}} [[Guglielmo Gabetto|Gabetto]]<br />{{Goal|67}} [[Armando Diena|Diena II]]\n|result =W\n}}\n{{footballbox collapsible\n|date = 6 July 1935\n|round = \n|time = \n|team1 = Juventus\n|team2 = {{flagicon|HUN}}[[MTK Hungaria]]\n|score = 1-1\n|report=\n|location = [[Torino]]\n|stadium = [[Stadio Olimpico Grande Torino|Stadio Benito Mussolini]]\n|attendance =\n|referee = {{flagicon|CSK}}J\u00e1n Biz\u00edk\n|goals1 = [[Giovanni Ferrari|Ferrari]] {{Goal|15}}\n|goals2 = {{Goal|48}} [[P\u00e1l Titkos|Titkos]]\n|result =D\n}}\n\n==== Semifinals ====\n{{footballbox collapsible\n|date = 16 July 1935\n|round = Andata\n|time = \n|team1 = {{flagicon|TCH}}[[Sparta Praha]]\n|team2 = Juventus\n|score = 2-0\n|report=\n|location = [[Praha]]\n|stadium = [[Stadion Letn\u00e1|Letensk\u00fd Stadion]]\n|attendance =\n|referee= {{flagicon|AUT}} Alois Beranek\n|goals1 = [[Ferdinand Faczinek|Faczinek]] {{Goal|43}}<br />[[Old\u0159ich Zaj\u00ed\u010dek|Zaj\u00ed\u010dek]] {{Goal|67|rig.}}\n|goals2 = \n|result =L\n}}\n\n{{footballbox collapsible\n|date = 21 July 1935\n|round = \n|time = \n|team1 = Juventus\n|team2 = {{flagicon|TCH}}[[Sparta Praha]]\n|score = 3-1\n|report=\n|location = [[Torino]]\n|stadium = [[Stadio Olimpico Grande Torino|Stadio Benito Mussolini]]\n|attendance =\n|referee = {{flagicon|HUN}} Mih\u00e1ly Iv\u00e1ncsics\n|goals1 = [[Gastone Prendato|Prendato]] {{Goal|1}}<br />[[Aldo Borel|Borel II]] {{Goal|52||90}}\n|goals2 = {{Goal|65}} [[Old\u0159ich Nejedl\u00fd|Nejedl\u00fd]]\n|result =W\n}}\n\n{{footballbox collapsible\n|date = 28 July 1935\t\n|round = Replay\n|time = \n|team1 = {{flagicon|TCH}}[[Sparta Praha]]\n|team2 = Juventus\n|score = 5-1\n|report=\n|location = [[Basel]]\n|stadium = [[Stadion Rankhof]]\n|attendance =\n|referee = {{flagicon|ENG}}Bert Fogg\n|goals1 = [[Old\u0159ich Zaj\u00ed\u010dek|Zaj\u00ed\u010dek]] {{Goal|21||87}}<br />[[Raymond Braine|Braine]] {{Goal|37||85}}<br />[[Ferdinand Faczinek|Faczinek]] {{Goal|40}}\n|goals2 = {{Goal|70|pen}} [[Alfredo Foni|Foni]]\n|result = L\n}}\n\n== Statistics ==\n=== Squad statistics ===\n<div style=\"font-size:90%\">\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:100%;margin:auto;clear:both;text-align:center;\"\n! rowspan=\"2\" | Competition<ref>{{cite book|title=Almanacco illustrato del calcio - La storia 1898-2004|author=Melegari|p= 92|language=Italian}}.</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.iffhs.de/?17f43c20e32b0ae63828ff2d17f92904a76056a31817f7370eff3702bb1c2bbb6a28e13c11e23b00e13c12|title=1935 Mitropa Cup|publisher=Iffhs.de}}</ref>\n! rowspan=\"2\" | Points\n! colspan=\"6\" | Home\n! colspan=\"6\" | Away\n! colspan=\"6\" | Total\n! rowspan=\"2\" | [[Goal average|GD]]\n|-